## Severity
Minor
## Dimension
kiss
## Location
src/proxy.rs:764-813
## Violation
compact_request_context performs an awkward dance to layer per-model config on top of the global compactor config:

  let mut compactor = ContextCompactor::for_model(&request.model);
  let base_config = state.compactor.config().clone();
  let mut model_config = compactor.config().clone();
  model_config.preserve_recent = base_config.preserve_recent;
  model_config.preserve_system = base_config.preserve_system;
  model_config.preserve_tool_calls = base_config.preserve_tool_calls;
  compactor.set_config(model_config);

The merge is hand-rolled — only three fields are pulled from base; any new CompactionConfig field added later will silently use the per-model default rather than operator overrides. This is a future maintenance footgun.
## Mandated refactor
Add CompactionConfig::merge(self, override_from: &CompactionConfig) -> Self that explicitly enumerates which fields are operator-overridable. Or invert: ContextCompactor::for_model_with_config(model: &str, base: CompactionConfig). Keep the field list in one place.
